The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing sparse or compressible signals from compressed sensing measurements that have undergone nonuniform quantization. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also introduces a new reconstruction approach, which involves minimizing the sparsity of the reconstructed signal under a weighted lp-norm fidelity constraint. This involves optimization techniques, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or mathematical optimization (cs.MM). Finally, the paper describes an efficient numerical procedure for computing the proposed approach, which could fall under numerical analysis (cs.NA).
